\newcommand{\NJFUDateText}{\number\year 年 \number\month 月 \number\day 日}

\newcommand{\NJFUChineseAbstract}{本文聚焦环巢湖湿地植被面临的“水文-污染-生物-空间”多重威胁，以生态系统韧性提升与可持续发展为目标，通过实地监测（2018-2024年）、数据量化分析（植被覆盖度、生物多样性、污染物拦截率）及典型案例实证（十八联圩、巢湖半岛湿地），识别了水利扰序、物种入侵、污染承压、生境破碎四大核心胁迫因子的作用机制。基于“问题-对策-验证”逻辑，构建“生态修复-工程调控-源头治理-社会参与”四维修复方案，提出梯度植被重建、智慧水文调度、多层污染拦截、社区共治共享等具体措施，并通过烔炀河、槐林湿地试点验证：方案实施后沉水植物恢复面积提升12.5倍，鸟类多样性增长35\%，氮磷拦截率达32\%。研究成果可为环巢湖湿地生态保护提供实操依据，亦为长江中下游淡水湖滨湿地植被修复与生态福祉提升提供范式参考。}

\newcommand{\NJFUChineseKeywords}{环巢湖湿地，植被危机，生态修复，四维方案，生态福祉}

\newcommand{\NJFUEnglishTitle}{Study on the Crisis Resolution and Ecological Welfare of Vegetation in Chaohu Lake Wetlands}

\newcommand{\NJFUEnglishAbstract}{This study focuses on the ``hydrological-pollution-biological-spatial'' multiple threats faced by vegetation in Chaohu Lake Wetlands, aiming at enhancing ecosystem resilience and sustainable development. Through field monitoring (2018--2024), quantitative data analysis (vegetation coverage, biodiversity, pollutant interception rate) and typical case verification (Shibalianwei, Chaohu Peninsula Wetlands), the mechanism of four core stress factors---hydrological disturbance, species invasion, pollution pressure, and habitat fragmentation---was identified. Based on the ``problem-countermeasure-verification'' logic, a four-dimensional restoration scheme of ``ecological restoration-engineering regulation-source governance-community participation'' was constructed, proposing specific measures such as gradient vegetation reconstruction, intelligent hydrological scheduling, multi-layer pollution interception, and community co-governance. Verified by pilot projects in Tongyang River and Huailin Wetlands: after the implementation of the scheme, the recovery area of submerged plants increased by 12.5 times, bird diversity increased by 35\%, and nitrogen and phosphorus interception rate reached 32\%. The research results can provide practical basis for ecological protection of Chaohu Lake Wetlands, and also serve as a paradigm reference for vegetation restoration and ecological welfare improvement of freshwater lakeside wetlands in the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River.}

\newcommand{\NJFUEnglishKeywords}{Chaohu Lake Wetlands, Vegetation Crisis, Ecological Restoration, Four-Dimensional Scheme, Ecological Welfare}

